this observational study that no significant differences were found in the 
different male treatment groups. All female body composition parameters 
initially showed lower values (<3 years HAART). The female treatment group (>3 
years HAART) displayed values similar to that seen in the HAART-naïve group. 
Higher W:H ratios in females receiving longer-term HAART potentially increases 
their risk for the future onset of cardio-metabolic complications.

